I want to know all about it . 
And here's Bock ! she cried . 
Dad says he's the greatest dog in the world , named after Botticelli or somebody . 
I've brought him a present . 
Nice old Bocky ! Bock , who was unaccustomed to spats , was examining them after his own fashion . 
Well , my dear , said Mrs. Mifflin . 
We are delighted to see you . 
I hope you'll be happy with us , but I rather doubt it . 
Mr. Mifflin is a hard man to get along with . 
Oh , I'm sure of it ! cried Titania . 
I mean , I'm sure I shall be happy ! You mustn't believe a word of what Dad says about me . 
I don't see how you can bear to sell them . 
I brought these violets for you , Mrs. Mifflin . 
How perfectly sweet of you , said Helen , captivated already . 
