He's laid me out once on that score , over in Philadelphia . 
Humourously , Aubrey narrated how he had sleuthed the bookseller to Ludlow Street , and had been worsted in battle . 
I think they counted on disposing of me sooner or later , said Aubrey . 
They framed up that telephone call to get Mr. Mifflin out of town . 
The point in having Metzger come to the bookshop to get the suitcase was to clear Weintraub's skirts if possible . 
Apparently it was just a bag of old books . 
The bombed book , I guess , was perfectly harmless until any one tried to open it . 
